# 🧱 GLOBAL ENGINEERING RULES

You are building a production-ready SaaS Beta for Meta Ads Monitoring + Spy Tool.

Strictly follow these rules.

---

## 1️⃣ Development Philosophy

- Build ONE module at a time.
- Do NOT move to the next module unless:
  - Current module compiles
  - No TypeScript errors
  - Unit tests written
  - Integration test written
  - All tests passing
- Refactor before proceeding.
- No placeholder logic.
- No fake/mock production logic.

---

## 2️⃣ Architecture Rules

Use Clean Architecture:

Controller → Service → Repository → Database

Rules:

- No business logic inside controllers.
- No direct DB calls inside controllers.
- All external APIs must go through Service layer.
- Repository layer handles Supabase interaction only.
- Every module must be independently testable.

---

## 3️⃣ Tech Stack (Non-Negotiable)

Frontend:
- Next.js (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind
- Zustand
- Recharts

Backend:
- Next.js API Routes
- TypeScript
- Supabase (PostgreSQL)
- Zod (validation)
- Jest (testing)

---

## 4️⃣ Folder Structure

/src
  /app
  /components
  /modules
      /auth
      /meta
      /monitoring
      /adspy
      /ai
  /services
  /repositories
  /lib
  /types
/tests

Each module must contain:

controller.ts
service.ts
repository.ts
types.ts
validation.ts
/tests

---

## 5️⃣ Type Safety Rules

- Strict TypeScript mode enabled.
- No `any` types.
- All API inputs validated using Zod.
- All external API responses validated before usage.

---

## 6️⃣ Supabase Rules

- All DB writes must be inside transactions where applicable.
- Use Row Level Security (RLS).
- Enforce user ownership on all data queries.
- Never expose service role key to frontend.
- Use server-side Supabase client for privileged actions.

---

## 7️⃣ Security Rules

- Encrypt Meta access tokens before storing.
- Store token expiry and implement refresh logic.
- Rate limit:
  - AI endpoints
  - Spy search endpoint
- Validate user ownership before returning data.
- No client-side secrets.

---

## 8️⃣ AI Usage Rules

AI is allowed ONLY for:

- Weekly Summary generation
- Creative Tagging (manual click only)

AI is NOT allowed for:

- Health scoring
- Metric calculation
- Trend detection
- Dashboard rendering

AI must:
- Receive structured JSON
- Return strict JSON schema
- Be validated before saving

Max tokens: 300 per request.

---

## 9️⃣ Testing Rules

Before completing any module:

- Unit tests for:
  - Services
  - Rule engines
  - AI schema validation
- Integration test for:
  - DB operations
  - API route
- Mock:
  - Meta API
  - AI API
  - Email service

Minimum coverage: 80%

If coverage < 80%, do not proceed.

---

## 🔟 Logging Rules

- Log all external API errors.
- Log token refresh failures.
- Do not expose internal errors to frontend.
- Use structured logging format.

---

## 11️⃣ Deployment Rules

- No console.log in production.
- All environment variables validated on startup.
- App must build without warnings.
- Production build must pass tests.

---

Violation of any rule requires fixing before new feature development.